<page>
   <topic>*AVERAGE Function</topic>
   <description>Get the average of a cr-lf delimited numbers.</description>
   
   <syntax>Average as N = *AVERAGE(C list_on_values)</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>Average</name>
         <description>Numerical average of values.</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>list_on_values</name>
         <description>Delimited list of values.</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
   
   <discussion>
The *AVERAGE() function returns the numerical average of a delimited list of numbers.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
dim list as C = "1,3,5,10"
? *average(list)
= 4.75
dim list2 as C
list2 = <<%a%
1
2
5
10
%a%
? *average(list2)
= 4.5

]]></example>
  
